ashion Glossary is our long-standing commitment to drive change in the world of fashion, design, and style, bringing together academic rigour and Condé Nast’s diverse point of view.</p><br />  <p>It has been created by Condé Nast, in partnership with the Centre for Sustainable Fashion, London College of Fashion, University of Arts London.</p></div></div></div></div><span class="jsx-c0c74ea4ac505846 checker absolute"></span></section><header class="jsx-d7573be8087300ff bg-white flex flex-wrap items-center w-full sticky  transition-top duration-500 up"><div class="jsx-d7573be8087300ff  flex flex-wrap items-center w-full"><nav class="jsx-d7573be8087300ff overflow-x-auto w-full pr-4"><div class="jsx-d7573be8087300ff mb-0 overflow-nav-group flex snap-mandatory snap-x py-4 px-8"><select class="jsx-d7573be8087300ff mr-8 font-label"><option selected="" value="0" class="jsx-d7573be8087300ff">Topic</option><option value="1" class="jsx-d7573be8087300ff">A-Z</option></select><a class="jsx-d7573be8087300ff mr-8 font-label item" href="/glossary/introduction">Introduction</a><a class="jsx-d7573be8087300ff mr-8 font-label item" href="/glossary/climate-emergency">Climate Emergency</a><a class="jsx-d7573be8087300ff mr-8 font-label item" href="/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion">Environmental Impacts of Fashion</a><a class="jsx-d7573be8087300ff mr-8 font-label item" href="/glossary/social-cultural-and-economic-impacts-of-fashion">Social, Cultural And Economic Impacts Of Fashion</a><a class="jsx-d7573be8087300ff mr-8 font-label item" href="/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability">Key Elements Of Fashion And Sustainability</a><a class="jsx-d7573be8087300ff mr-8 font-label item" href="/glossary/data-sources">Data Sources</a></div></nav></div></header><div class="jsx-d7573be8087300ff"></div><p class="jsx-d7573be8087300ff font-small max-w-titles px-4 py-4 mx-auto pb-20">The Sustainable Fashion Glossary is co-created by Condé Nast and Centre for Sustainable Fashion, Lon