y\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e. The process of \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/vocabulary-of-fashion-and-sustainability/dyeing\"\u003e\u003ci\u003edyeing\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e is also a major source of \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/water-pollution\"\u003e\u003ci\u003ewater pollution\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, as many textile-producing regions lack adequate environmental and health \u0026amp; safety legislation. As a result, unfiltered wastewater is often discharged into local waterways. This causes serious environmental and \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/health-hazards\"\u003e\u003ci\u003ehealth hazards\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, aggravated by the fact that many dyes contain \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/heavy-metals\"\u003e\u003ci\u003eheavy metals\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e such as lead or cadmium and some can break down into carcinogenic compounds. Further concerns are linked to the continuous release of such substances through domestic laundering.\u003csup\u003e(1-4)\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eSee also: \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/chemicals\"\u003eChemicals\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/hazardous-chemicals\"\u003eHazardous chemicals\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/chromium\"\u003eChromium\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/manufacturing-restricted-substance-list-mrsl-and-restricted-substance-list-rsl\"\u003eManufacturing Restricted Substance List (MRSL)\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/zero-discharge-of-h