ion/microfiber-pollution\"\u003e\u003ci\u003emicrofiber pollution\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and the release of \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/climate-emergency/microplastics\"\u003e\u003ci\u003emicroplastics\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, which endanger marine \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/climate-emergency/wildlife\"\u003e\u003ci\u003ewildlife\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and human health.\u003csup\u003e(1-6)\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eSee also: \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/climate-emergency/carbon-footprint\"\u003eCarbon footprint\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/hazardous-chemicals\"\u003eHazardous chemicals\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/environmental-costs\"\u003eEnvironmental costs\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/water-pollution\"\u003eWater pollution\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/blend-materials\"\u003eBlend materials\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/recycled-materials\"\u003eRecycled materials\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","references":"\u003col\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://mistrafuturefashion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Roos-D2.1.1.1-Fiber-Bible-Part-1_Mistra-Future-Fashion-2019.02-1.pdf\"\u003eMISTRA Future Fashion (2019 (2)). Possible sustainable fibers on the market and their technical properties. The Fiber Bible Part 1.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://mistrafuturefashion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Sandin-D2.12.1-Fiber-Bibel-Part-2_Mistra-Future-Fashion-Report-2019.03.pdf\"\u003eMISTRA Future Fashion (2019 (3)). Environmental impact of textile fibers – what we know and what we don’t know