 Economy Global Commitment – 2019 Progress Report.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","hideFromFeed":false,"createdAt":"2023-10-09T00:31:02.927Z","updatedAt":"2023-10-09T00:31:15.224Z","publishedAt":"2023-02-23T11:19:40.758Z","locale":"en"},{"id":4425,"title":"Water pollution","slug":"water-pollution","text":"\u003cp\u003eWater pollution refers to the contamination of water streams, lakes, oceans, groundwater, and sources of drinking water due to human activity. The role of fashion in water pollution is linked to run offs of pesticides and fertilizers used in the production of \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/natural-materials\"\u003e\u003ci\u003enatural materials\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and the contamination of waterways with toxic \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/chemicals\"\u003e\u003ci\u003echemicals\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e from all stages of textile production, including processes such as \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/dyeing\"\u003e\u003ci\u003edyeing\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/finishing\"\u003e\u003ci\u003efinishing\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e. Further pollution is caused by the release of chemicals and \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/climate-emergency/microplastics\"\u003e\u003ci\u003emicroplastics\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e during the use phase of clothing, especially through domestic \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/laundering\"\u003e\u003ci\u003elaundering\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e. Large volumes of unsold and used clothing deposited in \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/landfill\"\u003e\u003ci\u003elandfills\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e cause further water damage through leakages into waterways. The Citarum river in Indonesia, with over 200 textile factories along its riverbank, is considered the most polluted river in the world.\u003csup\u003e(1,2)\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eSee also: \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/synthetic-materials\"\u003eSynthetic materials\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/cotton\"\u003eCotton\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/dyes\"\u003eDyes\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/water-use\"\u003eWater use\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/water-scarcity\"\u003eWater scarcity\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/climate-emergency/global-inequality\"\u003eGlobal inequality\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/microfiber-pollution\"\u003eMicrofiber pollution\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/hazardous-chemicals\"\u003eHazardous chemicals\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/health-hazards\"\u003eHealth hazards\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/climate-emergency/biodiversity\"\u003eBiodiversity\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","references":"\u003col\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.wrap.org.uk/sites/files/wrap/valuing-our-clothes-the-cost-of-uk-fashion_WRAP.pdf\"\u003eWRAP (2017). Valuing Our Clothes: The cost of UK fashion.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://openknowledge.worldbank.org/bitstream/handle/10986/17750/851940WSP0Box300West0Java0Indonesia.pdf?sequence=1\u0026amp;isAllow