3c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and population growth (UN projections: 8.5 billion in 2030, 9.7 billion in 2050, 10.9 billion in 2100).\u003csup\u003e(1)\u003c/sup\u003e The 2019 World Economic Forum Global Risks report lists water crisis as one of the most critical concerns for the next decade.\u003csup\u003e(3-5)\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eSee also: \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/water-pollution\"\u003eWater pollution\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/cotton\"\u003eCotton\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/climate-emergency/global-inequality\"\u003eGlobal inequality\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/climate-emergency/global-warming\"\u003eGlobal warming\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/climate-emergency/climate-crisis\"\u003eClimate crisis\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/climate-emergency/biodiversity\"\u003eBiodiversity\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/climate-emergency/extinction\"\u003eExtinction\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","references":"\u003col\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://population.un.org/wpp/Publications/Files/WPP2019_Highlights.pdf\"\u003eUnited Nations (2019). World Population Prospects 2019.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://advances.sciencemag.org/content/advances/2/2/e1500323.full.pdf\"\u003eMekonnen, M.M. \u0026amp; Hoestra (2016). Four billion people facing severe water scarcity. \u003ci\u003eScience Advances\u003c/i\u003e, 2:e1500323.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www3.weforum.org/docs/WEF_Global_Risks_Report_2019.pdf\"\u003eWorld Economic Forum (2019). The Global Risks Report 2019.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.worldbank.org/en/topic/water\"\u0