ndenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/growth\"\u003e\u003ci\u003egrowth\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and depletion of natural resources, as both critically endanger all levels of prosperity for future generations.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eSee also: \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/growth\"\u003eGrowth\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/post-growth-economy\"\u003ePost-growth economy\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/well-being\"\u003eWell-being\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/systems-thinking\"\u003eSystems thinking\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/paradigm-change\"\u003eParadigm change\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/systems-change\"\u003eSystems change\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/sustainable-development\"\u003eSustainable development\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","references":"\u003col\u003e\u003cli\u003eSchumacher, E. F. (1993\u003ca href=\"\"\u003e1973\u003c/a\u003e). Small is Beautiful: A Study of Economics as if People Mattered. London: Vintage.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eStiglitz, J. E. et al. (2010). Mismeasuring our Lives: Why GDP Doesn’t Add Up. New York: The New Press.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eJackson, T. (2017\u003ca href=\"\"\u003e2009\u003c/a\u003e). Prosperity without growth : Foundations for the economy of tomorrow. London: Routledge.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ol\u003e","hideFromFeed":false,"createdAt":"2023-10-09T00:00:24.620Z","updatedAt":"2023-10-09T00:00:28.386Z","publishedAt":"2023-02-23T12:26:02.162Z","locale":"en"},{"id":2985,"title":"Textile industry","slug":"textile-industry","text":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:rgb(45,46,47);\"\u003eSee \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/fashion-industry\"\u003eFashion industry\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:rgb(45,46,47);\"\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","references":null,"hideFromFeed":false,"createdAt":"2023-10-09T00:00:28.865Z","updatedAt":"2023-10-09T00:00:32.784Z","publishedAt":"2023-02-23T12:35:01.800Z","locale":"en"},{"id":2994,"title":"4.2 Fashion industry","slug":"4-2-fashion-industry","text":null,"references":null,"hideFromFeed":false,"createdAt":"2023-10-09T00:00:33.275Z","updatedAt":"2023-10-09T00:00:37.808Z","publishedAt":"2023-02-23T12:31:06.073Z","locale":"en"},{"id":3021,"title":"Systems change","slug":"systems-change","text":"\u003cp\u003eSystems change refers to an intentional transformation of the ways in which a system, such as an organization, industry, society or economy operate. Systems change focuses on the root causes of problems, instead of investing time and resources in temporary fixes that can only treat symptoms. Systems change draws on \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/systems-thinking\"\u003e\u003ci\u003esystems thinking\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, a recognition that all systems consist of parts which relate to each other and influence the way the whole system behaves across time.\u003csup\u003e(1)\u003c/sup\u003e This is why any attempt at resolving issues within a system must rely on seeing it as a whole and addressing the underlying values and goals, instead of just “tweaking parameters”.\u003csup\u003e(2)\u003c/sup\u003e In the current \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/climate-emergency/climate-emergency\"\u003e\u003ci\u003eclimate emergency\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, fashion too urgently needs a systems change. It is now clear that the last thirty years of incremental changes in \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability#sustainable-materials\"\u003e\u003ci\u003esustainable materials\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, resource \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/efficiency\"\u003e\u003ci\u003eefficiency\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/recycling\"\u003e\u003ci\u003erecycling\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e did not bring about the desired results.\u003csup\u003e(2,5)\u003c/sup\u003e All such improvements are lost in a system where the volume of production, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/consumption\"\u003e\u003ci\u003econsumption\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, and \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/waste\"\u003e\u003ci\u003ewaste\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003egeneration constantly escalate.\u003csup\u003e(3)\u003c/sup\u003e What is therefore needed is a fundamental change in fashion’s current business model that relies on uninhibited \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/growth\"\u003e\u003ci\u003egrowth\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and results in exploitation of both people and the environment. We need to find new and richer ways of enjoying and giving value to fashion. \u003csup\u003e(1-5)\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eSee also: \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/paradigm-change\"\u003eParadigm change\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/sustainable-fashion\"\u003eSustainable fashion\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/post-growth-economy\"\u003ePost-growth economy\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/resilience\"\u003eResilience\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability#interdependence\"\u003eInterdependence\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","references":"\u003col\u003e\u003cli\u003eMeadows, D.H. (2009). Thinking in Systems: A Primer. London; Sterling, VA: Earthscan, p.1.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://earthlogic.info/\"\u003eFletcher, K. \u0026amp; Tham, M. (2019). Earth Logic: Fashion Action Research Plan. London: JJ Charitable Trust, p. 12.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201719/cmselect/cmenvaud/1952/1952.pdf\"\u003eHouse of Commons Environmental Audit Committee (2019 (16)). Fixing Fashion: Clothing consumption and sustainability, p. 37.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eFletcher, K. (2009). Systems change for sustainability in textiles. In R. Blackburn (Ed.) Sustainable Textiles. Oxford: Woodhead Publishing, pp. 369-380.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://concernedresearchers.org/ucrf-on-2019-copenhagen-fashion-summit/\"\u003eUnion of Concerned Researchers in Fashion (2019, May 5). Statement on 2019 Fashion Summit.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ol\u003e","hideFromFeed":false,"createdAt":"2023-10-09T00:00:46.614Z","updatedAt":"2023-10-09T00:00:50.810Z","publishedAt":"2023-02-23T12:28:29.461Z","locale":"en"},{"id":3030,"title":"Eco fashion","slug":"eco-fashion","text":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:rgb(45,46,47);\"\u003eSee \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/sustainable-fashion\"\u003eSustainable fashion\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:rgb(45,46,47);\"\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","references":null,"hideFromFeed":false,"createdAt":"2023-10-09T00:00:51.390Z","updatedAt":"2023-10-09T00:00:55.907Z","