ctured and their natural environment. In the wider sense of the global social and environmental impacts, the stakeholders of the fashion industry are people across the entire globe, the planet, and future generations.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eSee also: \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/care\"\u003eCare\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/respect\"\u003eRespect\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/corporate-social-responsibility-csr\"\u003eCorporate social responsibility (CSR)\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/interdependence\"\u003eInterdependence\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/sustainable-development\"\u003eSustainable development\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/users\"\u003eUsers\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability#trust\"\u003eTrust\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability#gen-y\"\u003eGen Y\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","references":"\u003cp\u003eFurther resources:\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.unglobalcompact.org.uk/the-ten-principles/\"\u003eUnited Nations Global Compact (2019). The Ten Principles.\u003c/a\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://www.unglobalcompact.org/docs/publications/AA_UNGC_Report.pdf\"\u003eAccountability \u0026amp; United Nations Global Compact (2013). Growing into Your Sustainability Commitments: A Roadmap for Impact and Value Creation.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","hideFromFeed":false,"createdAt":"2023-10-09T00:45:13.275Z","updatedAt":"2023-10-09T00:45:42.876Z","pub