re \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/supply-chain\"\u003e\u003ci\u003esupply chains\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, from raw materials sourcing to their own operations.\u003csup\u003e(1)\u003c/sup\u003e The commitment to ethical trade is reflected in policy-making as well as regular monitoring, auditing, reporting and acting on the responsibility for continuous improvement.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eSee also: \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/social-cultural-and-economic-impacts-of-fashion/transparency\"\u003eTransparency\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/social-cultural-and-economic-impacts-of-fashion/offshore-manufacture\"\u003eOffshore manufacture\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/social-cultural-and-economic-impacts-of-fashion/modern-slavery\"\u003eModern slavery\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/social-cultural-and-economic-impacts-of-fashion/living-wage\"\u003eLiving wage\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/social-cultural-and-economic-impacts-of-fashion/poverty\"\u003ePoverty\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/social-cultural-and-economic-impacts-of-fashion/social-costs\"\u003eSocial costs\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/social-cultural-and-economic-impacts-of-fashion/human-rights\"\u003eHuman rights\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/accountability\"\u003eAccountability\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/corporate-social-responsibility-csr\"\u003eCorporate social responsibility (CSR)\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/stakeholders\"\u003eStakeholders\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www