\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and passive depletion of resources,\u003csup\u003e(1)\u003c/sup\u003e to \"usership\", which instead draws satisfaction from experiences of long-term use that require time, attention and tending of the things we choose to buy and use.\u003csup\u003e(8)\u003c/sup\u003e We need to shift our perception of ourselves and each other from being solely identified as consumers to recognizing that we are all users and contributors to society, culture, environment and \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/economy\"\u003e\u003ci\u003eeconomy\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003ethrough our own skills, creativity, care and \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/respect\"\u003e\u003ci\u003erespect\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e for people and the environment worldwide.\u003csup\u003e(1-8)\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eSee also: \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/overconsumption\"\u003eOverconsumption\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/paradigm-change\"\u003eParadigm change\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/systems-thinking\"\u003eSystems thinking\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/systems-change\"\u003eSystems change\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/post-growth-economy\"\u003ePost-growth economy\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/sustainable-fashion\"\u003eSustainable fashion\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/post-growth-fashion\"\u003ePost-growth fashion\u003c/a\u