ategies that actively seek solutions for managing demand and reducing the volumes of production and consumption. These may include alternative business models that promote \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/extending-clothing-lifetimes\"\u003e\u003ci\u003eextending clothing lifetimes\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e through \u003ci\u003ere-use, \u003c/i\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/sharing\"\u003e\u003ci\u003esharing\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ci\u003e, rental\u003c/i\u003e or \u003ci\u003ere-sale\u003c/i\u003e and also through raising \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/public-awareness\"\u003e\u003ci\u003epublic awareness\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e of all such options.\u003csup\u003e(1,2)\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eSee also: \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/environmental-impacts-of-fashion/growth\"\u003eGrowth\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/paradigm-change\"\u003eParadigm change\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/systems-change\"\u003eSystems change\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/post-growth-economy\"\u003ePost-growth economy\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/prosperity\"\u003eProsperity\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/craft-of-use\"\u003eCraft of use\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/gen-y\"\u003eGen Y\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","references":"\u003col\u003e\u003cli\u003eFletcher, K. (2016). Craft of Use: 