ts-of-fashion-and-sustainability/chemicals\"\u003e\u003ci\u003echemical\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e use for each production stage. The GRS is one of the group of certifications by the global NGO Textile Exchange, also including the \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/organic-content-standard-ocs\"\u003e\u003ci\u003eOrganic Content Standard (OCS)\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and the \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/responsible-wool-standard-rws\"\u003e\u003ci\u003eResponsible Wool Standard (RWS)\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e.\u003csup\u003e(1-3)\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eSee also: \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/social-cultural-and-economic-impacts-of-fashion/greenwashing\"\u003eGreenwashing\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/recyclability\"\u003eRecyclability\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/non-virgin-materials\"\u003eNon-virgin materials\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/closed-loop-recycling\"\u003eClosed-loop recycling\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/circular-economy\"\u003eCircular economy\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.condenast.com/glossary/key-elements-of-fashion-and-sustainability/public-awareness\"\u003ePublic awareness\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","references":"\u003col\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://textileexchange.org/integrity/\"\u003eTextile Exchange Standards (2020).\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://textileexchange.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Global-Recycled-Standard-v4.0.pdf\"\u003eTextile Exchange (2017). Global Recycled Standard\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u